The issue with your code is that you are not closing the PrintWriter after writing to the file. You need to close the PrintWriter after you are done writing to the file. Add the following line after the last PrintWriter.write("anybody there?"); line:

print.close();

Here's the updated code:

<<<code>>>: public void savefile() throws IOException {
JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null,"Hi,i'm in Try Block :|");
FileWriter write = new FileWriter("asd.txt", true);
PrintWriter print = new PrintWriter(write);
JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "File Opened");
print.write("Knock Knock");
print.flush();
print.write("Hello ?");
print.flush();
print.printf("Hi?");
print.flush();
print.println("anybody there?");
print.flush();
JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "Can you hear me ?");
print.close();
JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "File Closed");
}

<<<explanation>>>: By adding the print.close(); line, you are closing the PrintWriter and flushing any remaining data from the writer to the file. This ensures that the file is properly closed and any data left in the writer is written to the file.
